## Water Chemistry by PWL ID

Calcium, The X-axis presents WI/PWL ID of the sampling locations from upstream to downstream and axis labels correspond with Table 1, Figure 1 and Figure 2. Color of the box represents the location of the WI/WPL in the watershed as indicated in the plot legend. Red horizontal lines represent the 95% confidence interval of statewide data for each endpoint. The total number of reported values illustrated for each sampling location can vary due to non-detection and QA/QC procedures. Descriptions of removed records are presented in Appendix III.
